2 Garlic
1 packet Roasted almonds
1 packet Single Cream Brie
1 packet Pitted Mixed Olives
1 Sourdough Loaf
2 packet Plant-Based Basil Pesto
80 g Prosciutto
1 Tomato
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
½ tbs honey
1 drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 drizzle olive oil

• Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced.
• Slice the sourdough loaf into 4 even slices. Toast or grill sourdough to your liking.
• Cut tomato into wedges. Thinly slice garlic.

• Score single cream brie in a crisscross pattern.
• Place brie in a small lined baking dish and press garlic into the slits.
• Drizzle with olive oil and the honey and bake, until softened, 5-7 minutes.
• When done, carefully transfer to serving board.

• In a medium bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, tomato, a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper.

• Arrange the baked brie, prosciutto, pitted mixed olives, roasted almonds, toasted sourdough, basil pesto and tomato salad on a serving platter. Enjoy!